The market segmentation based on product type highlights various key segments within the EDA market, including Computer-Aided Engineering (CAE), IC Physical Design and Verification, Printed Circuit Board and Multi-Chip Module (PCB and MCM), Semiconductor Intellectual Property (SIP), and others. Among these segments, IC Physical Design and Verification are expected to experience substantial growth due to the increasing complexity of integrated circuits and the escalating need for robust verification solutions. As integrated circuits become more intricate and sophisticated, the demand for efficient design and verification tools continues to surge, driving growth in this segment.

In terms of application segmentation, the EDA market caters to industries such as Aerospace and Defense, Automotive, Consumer Electronics, Industrial, Telecom, and others. The consumer electronics segment is anticipated to dominate the market share, fueled by the growing demand for smartphones, wearables, and other electronic gadgets worldwide. As consumers seek more advanced and feature-rich electronic devices, manufacturers are under pressure to innovate and deliver cutting-edge products, thereby driving the demand for EDA solutions in this segment.

